This article discusses the recent return of the remains of U.S. service members who went missing during the Korean War. Vice President Mike Pence attended a ceremony in Hawaii where 55 boxes containing the remains were brought back to American soil. Recovery efforts had been suspended for over a decade due to North Korea's nuclear threats, but President Trump's summit with North Korean leader Kim Jong-Un in June resulted in a commitment to return the remains. The article emphasizes the importance of honoring the fallen soldiers and fulfilling the promise to bring them home.